This paper discusses the use of large sense-annotated datasets for training deep supervised systems in Word Sense Disambiguation, which is a topic related to natural language processing and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper also discusses the use of different lexical resources such as WordNet, Wikipedia, and BabelNet, which are relevant to sub-categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
